{
  "texts": [
    "Here, x ′′ N n, where N is 1,2,3.. up to number of patches, represents the patches of a single instance in Eq. 6, and E is for the learnable embeddings.In contrast to patching, tokenization approach involves utilizing convolutional and pooling transformations for operations.",
    "Convolutional layers are used to process the data, extracting spatial information through convolutions and downsampling operations.",
    "These local features are then presented as tokens and passed into the transformer for additional processing.",
    "After applying convolutional operations, tokenization process produces patches with a 16 × 16 × 3 size, for a total of 64 patches.",
    "Tokenization process converts the images data into smaller tokens, as depicted in Eqs. 7 and 8."
  ]
}